<title>BRAZIL: Key Brazil ports say loading suspended due to rain.</title>
<headline>Key Brazil ports say loading suspended due to rain.</headline>
<dateline>SAO PAULO 1997-04-01</dateline>
<text>
<p>The key Brazilian ports of Paranagua and Santos said loading of grains at their export terminals had been temporarily suspended because of rain.</p>
<p>The export terminal at Santos shut at 1730 local/2030 GMT Monday and remained closed, the port authority said.</p>
<p>At Paranagua, operations were suspended at 0750 local Tuesday, an official at the export terminal said.  </p>
<p>The closures affect mainly the loading of grains. Loading of containers will continue. The grain loading facilities are expected to remain shut until the rain stops.</p>
<p>Rains are expected to continue on and off in the region of Santos for the next three days, said the National Institute of Meteorology (Inmet). &quot;From tomorrow there will be periods of sun and there is a possibility of a slight improvement later today,&quot; a forecaster said.</p>
<p>In Paranagua, the weather is likely to improve with sunshine predicted for most of Wednesday, Inmet said.</p>
<p>((--Joelle Diderich, Sao Paulo newsroom +55 11 248 5417))</p>
